{
  "texts": [
    "The list should be enclosed in brackets and separated by a comma, e.g.",
    "[True, False].",
    "\"The raw responses were stored and afterward, the two boolean values were extracted unless the extraction failed due to incorrect formatting.",
    "The results were evaluated against the ground truth by computing the proportion of correctly formatted predictions (i.e., a single integer or a list of two booleans in brackets separated by a comma) as well as the confusion matrices for each label and several performance metrics (accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score).All programming was performed in Python (version 3.11.5) using, among others, the pandas (version 2.1.0) and openai (version 1.40.3) packages.",
    "This article was previously posted to the medRxiv preprint server on October 23, 2024."
  ]
}